report_text: Patient shows symptoms: itching (severity 1), skin_rash (severity 3), nodal_skin_eruptions (severity 4), dischromic _patches (severity unknown). Disease: Fungal infection. Description: In humans, fungal infections occur when an invading fungus takes over an area of the body and is too much for the immune system to handle. Fungi can live in the air, soil, water, and plants. There are also some fungi that live naturally in the human body. Like many microbes, there are helpful fungi and harmful fungi.. Suggested precautions: bath twice, use detol or neem in bathing water, keep infected area dry, use clean cloths.

Patient shows symptoms: stomach_pain (severity 5), acidity (severity 3), ulcers_on_tongue (severity 4), vomiting (severity 5), cough (severity 4), chest_pain (severity 7). Disease: GERD. Description: Gastroesophageal reflux disease, or GERD, is a digestive disorder that affects the lower esophageal sphincter (LES), the ring of muscle between the esophagus and stomach. Many people, including pregnant women, suffer from heartburn or acid indigestion caused by GERD.. Suggested precautions: avoid fatty spicy food, avoid lying down after eating, maintain healthy weight, exercise.

Patient shows symptoms: back_pain (severity 3), weakness_in_limbs (severity 7), neck_pain (severity 5), dizziness (severity 4), loss_of_balance (severity 4). Disease: Cervical spondylosis. Description: Cervical spondylosis is a general term for age-related wear and tear affecting the spinal disks in your neck. As the disks dehydrate and shrink, signs of osteoarthritis develop, including bony projections along the edges of bones (bone spurs).. Suggested precautions: use heating pad or cold pack, exercise, take otc pain reliver, consult doctor.

Suggested precautions: use heating pad or cold pack, exercise, take otc pain reliver, consult doctor.

Disease: Jaundice. Description: Yellow staining of the skin and sclerae (the whites of the eyes) by abnormally high blood levels of the bile pigment bilirubin. The yellowing extends to other tissues and body fluids. Jaundice was once called the "morbus regius" (the regal disease) in the belief that only the touch of a king could cure it. Suggested precautions: drink plenty of water, consume milk thistle, eat fruits and high fiberous food, medication.

Patient shows symptoms: back_pain (severity 3), weakness_in_limbs (severity 7), neck_pain (severity 5), dizziness (severity 4), loss_of_balance (severity 4). Disease: Cervical spondylosis. Description: Cervical spondylosis is a general term for age-related wear and tear affecting the spinal disks in your neck. As the disks dehydrate and shrink, signs of osteoarthritis develop, including bony projections along the edges of bones (bone spurs).. Suggested precautions: use heating pad or cold pack, exercise, take otc pain reliver, consult doctor.

Patient shows symptoms: itching (severity 1), vomiting (severity 5), fatigue (severity 4), weight_loss (severity 3), high_fever (severity 7), yellowish_skin (severity 3), dark_urine (severity 4), abdominal_pain (severity 4). Disease: Jaundice. Description: Yellow staining of the skin and sclerae (the whites of the eyes) by abnormally high blood levels of the bile pigment bilirubin. The yellowing extends to other tissues and body fluids. Jaundice was once called the "morbus regius" (the regal disease) in the belief that only the touch of a king could cure it. Suggested precautions: drink plenty of water, consume milk thistle, eat fruits and high fiberous food, medication.

The yellowing extends to other tissues and body fluids. Jaundice was once called the "morbus regius" (the regal disease) in the belief that only the touch of a king could cure it. Suggested precautions: drink plenty of water, consume milk thistle, eat fruits and high fiberous food, medication.

Suggested precautions: lie down on side, check in pulse, drink sugary drinks, consult doctor.

Suggested precautions: wash hands with warm soapy water, stop bleeding using pressure, consult doctor, salt baths.

Description: Impetigo (im-puh-TIE-go) is a common and highly contagious skin infection that mainly affects infants and children. Impetigo usually appears as red sores on the face, especially around a child's nose and mouth, and on hands and feet. The sores burst and develop honey-colored crusts.. Suggested precautions: soak affected area in warm water, use antibiotics, remove scabs with wet compressed cloth, consult doctor.

Patient shows symptoms: back_pain (severity 3), weakness_in_limbs (severity 7), neck_pain (severity 5), dizziness (severity 4), loss_of_balance (severity 4). Disease: Cervical spondylosis. Description: Cervical spondylosis is a general term for age-related wear and tear affecting the spinal disks in your neck. As the disks dehydrate and shrink, signs of osteoarthritis develop, including bony projections along the edges of bones (bone spurs).. Suggested precautions: use heating pad or cold pack, exercise, take otc pain reliver, consult doctor.

Patient shows symptoms: itching (severity 1), vomiting (severity 5), fatigue (severity 4), weight_loss (severity 3), high_fever (severity 7), yellowish_skin (severity 3), dark_urine (severity 4), abdominal_pain (severity 4). Disease: Jaundice. Description: Yellow staining of the skin and sclerae (the whites of the eyes) by abnormally high blood levels of the bile pigment bilirubin. The yellowing extends to other tissues and body fluids. Jaundice was once called the "morbus regius" (the regal disease) in the belief that only the touch of a king could cure it. Suggested precautions: drink plenty of water, consume milk thistle, eat fruits and high fiberous food, medication.

Patient shows symptoms: skin_rash (severity 3), joint_pain (severity 3), skin_peeling (severity 3), silver_like_dusting (severity 2), small_dents_in_nails (severity 2), inflammatory_nails (severity 2). Disease: Psoriasis. Description: Psoriasis is a common skin disorder that forms thick, red, bumpy patches covered with silvery scales. They can pop up anywhere, but most appear on the scalp, elbows, knees, and lower back. Psoriasis can't be passed from person to person. It does sometimes happen in members of the same family.. Suggested precautions: wash hands with warm soapy water, stop bleeding using pressure, consult doctor, salt baths.

Patient shows symptoms: skin_rash (severity 3), high_fever (severity 7), blister (severity 4), red_sore_around_nose (severity 2), yellow_crust_ooze (severity 3). Disease: Impetigo. Description: Impetigo (im-puh-TIE-go) is a common and highly contagious skin infection that mainly affects infants and children. Impetigo usually appears as red sores on the face, especially around a child's nose and mouth, and on hands and feet. The sores burst and develop honey-colored crusts.. Suggested precautions: soak affected area in warm water, use antibiotics, remove scabs with wet compressed cloth, consult doctor.

Description: Impetigo (im-puh-TIE-go) is a common and highly contagious skin infection that mainly affects infants and children. Impetigo usually appears as red sores on the face, especially around a child's nose and mouth, and on hands and feet. The sores burst and develop honey-colored crusts.. Suggested precautions: soak affected area in warm water, use antibiotics, remove scabs with wet compressed cloth, consult doctor.

Patient shows symptoms: back_pain (severity 3), weakness_in_limbs (severity 7), neck_pain (severity 5), dizziness (severity 4), loss_of_balance (severity 4). Disease: Cervical spondylosis. Description: Cervical spondylosis is a general term for age-related wear and tear affecting the spinal disks in your neck. As the disks dehydrate and shrink, signs of osteoarthritis develop, including bony projections along the edges of bones (bone spurs).. Suggested precautions: use heating pad or cold pack, exercise, take otc pain reliver, consult doctor.

Disease: Jaundice. Description: Yellow staining of the skin and sclerae (the whites of the eyes) by abnormally high blood levels of the bile pigment bilirubin. The yellowing extends to other tissues and body fluids. Jaundice was once called the "morbus regius" (the regal disease) in the belief that only the touch of a king could cure it. Suggested precautions: drink plenty of water, consume milk thistle, eat fruits and high fiberous food, medication.

Patient shows symptoms: skin_rash (severity 3), high_fever (severity 7), blister (severity 4), red_sore_around_nose (severity 2), yellow_crust_ooze (severity 3). Disease: Impetigo. Description: Impetigo (im-puh-TIE-go) is a common and highly contagious skin infection that mainly affects infants and children. Impetigo usually appears as red sores on the face, especially around a child's nose and mouth, and on hands and feet. The sores burst and develop honey-colored crusts.. Suggested precautions: soak affected area in warm water, use antibiotics, remove scabs with wet compressed cloth, consult doctor.

Patient shows symptoms: back_pain (severity 3), weakness_in_limbs (severity 7), neck_pain (severity 5), dizziness (severity 4), loss_of_balance (severity 4). Disease: Cervical spondylosis. Description: Cervical spondylosis is a general term for age-related wear and tear affecting the spinal disks in your neck. As the disks dehydrate and shrink, signs of osteoarthritis develop, including bony projections along the edges of bones (bone spurs).. Suggested precautions: use heating pad or cold pack, exercise, take otc pain reliver, consult doctor.
